data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","sequence_number":366,"item_id":"msg_085ece70d34dba8f00693b2df2ce10819388dfa92679f1f382","output_index":4,"content_index":0,"text":"It depends on the system, but generally a “secondary agent” can do one or more of the following roles and tasks:\n\nCommon capabilities\n- Failover/backup: take over the primary’s duties automatically or manually if the primary becomes unavailable.\n- Load-sharing: handle overflow traffic or non-critical requests to reduce primary load.\n- Specialized processing: perform dedicated subtasks (e.g., inference, scoring, heavy computation, data enrichment) that are split off from the primary.\n- Monitoring and health checks: watch system health, collect metrics, and raise alerts for the primary or ops team.\n- Retry and error handling: accept tasks that need retries, remediation, or slower processing so the primary stays responsive.\n- Logging, auditing, and telemetry: record detailed logs, produce audit trails, and aggregate metrics for observability.\n- Orchestration/support functions: manage queues, schedule jobs, coordinate multi-step workflows, or hand off tasks between components.\n- Testing/staging: run canary tests, validation, or QA steps before changes reach the primary agent or production.\n- Security-limited actions: operate with restricted permissions for sensitive or high-risk operations (least privilege).\n\nTypical constraints and behaviors\n- Lower privileges or narrower scope than the primary (so it can’t perform everything).\n- May be eventual-consistent or asynchronous (not real-time).\n- Usually designed for reliability and isolation—less likely to cause system-wide disruption.\n- Often focused on resiliency and observability rather than full-feature parity.\n\nIf you tell me the context (e.g., cloud service failover, chatbots with primary/secondary agents, distributed robotics, CI/CD pipelines), I can list specific responsibilities, example configurations, or a recommended design for the secondary agent. What system are you working with?","logprobs":[]}

